# Satellite env – copy from thebzlab satellite compose (Codelovers satellite will use these when you run set-dokploy-env.mjs)
#
# 1. Open: https://dokploy.thebzlab.online/dashboard/project/Iztezrz8wKhWurhwd6jJe/environment/XtSnvEh7LIZURw2-eLRRW/services/compose/MvWG0N6Zyg7IRAmtGxhIu
# 2. Sign in, open the satellite compose → Environment
# 3. Copy the values below and paste here. Save as .env.dokploy.satellite (no .example)
# 4. Run: node scripts/set-dokploy-env.mjs
#
# GEE (Google Earth Engine)
GEE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT=
GEE_PRIVATE_KEY=
GEE_PROJECT_ID=sublime-seat-428722-n5
#
# CDSE (Copernicus Data Space) – optional if using CDSE provider
CDSE_CLIENT_ID=
CDSE_CLIENT_SECRET=
